{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 07:04:38.050924", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission details\n- Anomaly detected: Yes\n- Faulty devices:\n  - web_server_0 (10.200.0.3)\n  - web_server_1 (10.200.0.4)\n  - web_server_2 (10.200.0.5)\n  - web_server_3 (10.200.0.6)\n  - 20.200.0.2\n  - 20.200.0.3\n  - 20.200.0.4\n- Root cause:\n  - sender_application_delay\n\nRationale\n- All public and backend web servers are running Python’s BaseHTTP server instead of Apache as designed, returning 501 to HEAD and exhibiting ~1 s total request times despite healthy network metrics. This is consistent with an application-layer issue (sender_application_delay) rather than a network/routing fault.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2306, "output_tokens": 183, "total_tokens": 2489, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2176}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
